In a #small pot{}, bring 1 1/2 cups water (2 1/2 cups for 4 servings), half the @Pearl Barley{3/4%cup} (all for 4), half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest later), and a big pinch of @salt{pinch} to a boil. Once boiling, reduce to a low simmer; cover and cook until tender and most of the water has absorbed, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Drain if necessary; keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While barley cooks, wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and finely dice @Yellow Onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Trim, peel, and halve @Carrots{6%oz} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise. Trim and thinly slice @Button Mushrooms{4%oz} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!).

Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%tsp} in a #large pot{} over medium heat. Add onion, carrots, mushrooms, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and tender, ~{4-7%minutes}.

Increase heat under pot to medium high. Add @Ground Beef{10%oz}, remaining Fry Seasoning, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add @Tomato Paste{1.5%oz} and cook, stirring often, until fragrant and darkened in color, ~{30-60%seconds}.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Stir 3 cups water (6 cups for 4 servings), @Beef Stock Concentrate{2}, and @Mushroom Stock Concentrate{1} into pot. Bring to a boil; cook, stirring occasionally, until soup has slightly reduced and beef is cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes}. Skim off any fat from the surface if necessary. Keep soup covered off heat.

Stir cooked barley into pot with soup. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide between #bowls{} and serve.